-- 29-bootstrapper-frames.cell — full eval-one execution trace
--
-- Ready set analysis:
--   task: all givens have ≡ → READY
--   analyze-needs: needs task→prompt → BLOCKED
--   spawn-specialists: needs analyze-needs→needed-cells → BLOCKED
--   specialist-*: spawned dynamically → BLOCKED
--   synthesize: needs specialist-*→findings → BLOCKED
--   evaluate-completeness: needs synthesize→draft-plan → BLOCKED
--   spawn-gap-fillers: needs evaluate-completeness→gaps → BLOCKED
--   gap-filler-*: spawned dynamically → BLOCKED
--   re-synthesize: needs gap-filler-*→additional-findings → BLOCKED
--   final-plan: needs re-synthesize→revised-plan → BLOCKED
--   bootstrapper-observations: no givens → READY (deterministic)
--
-- Ready set: { task, bootstrapper-observations }
--
-- Structure: BOOTSTRAP SPINE with TWO FAN-OUT waves.
--   task → analyze-needs → spawn-specialists
--     → [specialist-1..N] → synthesize → evaluate-completeness
--       → spawn-gap-fillers → [gap-filler-1..M] → re-synthesize
--         → (⊢∘ loop back to evaluate if quality < 7)
--           → final-plan
--
-- The key insight: the program starts with ZERO domain cells.
-- analyze-needs decides what cells to create. spawn-specialists creates them.
-- evaluate-completeness decides if MORE cells are needed. Frontier grows
-- dynamically until convergence.

