⊢= bootstrapper-observations
  yield observations

  yield observations ≡ "
    1. ZERO-START BOOTSTRAP: This program begins with no domain cells at all.
       The meta-cell (analyze-needs) inspects the task and DECIDES what cells
       to create. This is the purest form of Cell's self-bootstrapping property.

    2. TWO-PHASE SPAWNING: First wave (spawn-specialists) creates broad coverage.
       Second wave (spawn-gap-fillers) creates targeted depth. The meta-cell
       reasons about what's MISSING, not just what's NEEDED.

    3. CONVERGENCE VIA ⊢∘: The evolution loop doesn't improve a single cell —
       it improves the ENSEMBLE. Each iteration spawns new cells into the
       frontier, making the collective output more complete. The quality-score
       oracle drives convergence.

    4. TEMPLATE POLYMORPHISM: specialist-template and gap-filler-template are
       the same shape (given context → yield findings + recommendations) but
       serve different roles. The spawner binds different purposes to the
       same interface. This is Cell's version of parametric polymorphism.

    5. META-REASONING: analyze-needs must reason about reasoning — what KINDS
       of knowledge does this task require? This is the bootstrapping insight:
       the system must be able to reflect on its own capabilities gap.

    6. MONOTONIC GROWTH: The plan only gets better. re-synthesize is a superset
       of synthesize. Information accumulates, never retracts. This matches
       Cell's monotonicity guarantee at the language level.
  "

