-- LLM evaluation:

  yield findings ≡ "Tokyo architecture spans 1400 years of building culture and contains some of the world's most important modern buildings.

MODERN: (1) Omotesando — 'Tokyo's Champs-Élysées' but for architecture. Every luxury brand hired a starchitect: Tadao Ando (Omotesando Hills), SANAA (Dior), Toyo Ito (Tod's), Herzog & de Meuron (Prada — the crystalline glass building). Walkable in 1-2 hours. (2) Roppongi — 21_21 Design Sight (Tadao Ando), National Art Center (Kisho Kurokawa — undulating glass facade), Mori Tower observation deck. (3) Ginza — Nakagin Capsule Tower was demolished 2022 but its site is marked; Ginza Six (MVRDV rooftop garden); Shizuoka Press Building (Kenzo Tange, metabolism). (4) Shibuya — Shibuya Stream and Scramble Square, Miyashita Park redevelopment. (5) Shinjuku — Mode Gakuen Cocoon Tower (most photogenic skyscraper in Tokyo), Tokyo Metropolitan Government Building (Kenzo Tange, free observation deck).

TRADITIONAL: (1) Meiji Jingu — massive Shinto shrine, forested grounds in the middle of the city. Weekend ceremonies possible. (2) Senso-ji — oldest temple in Tokyo, Asakusa. Tourist-heavy but architecturally significant (Thunder Gate, five-story pagoda). (3) Nezu Shrine — vermillion torii gates, quieter than Meiji. (4) Imperial Palace East Gardens — free, Edo castle ruins, peaceful. (5) Yoyogi National Gymnasium (Kenzo Tange, 1964 Olympics — brutalist masterwork, visible from outside).

Weekend considerations: Most outdoor sites accessible 24/7. Museums/galleries typically closed Tuesdays, open weekends. Omotesando shops open 11am-8pm weekends."

  yield recommendations ≡ [
    "Day 1 morning: Omotesando architecture walk — Prada, Tod's, Omotesando Hills. Free, self-guided, 1.5 hours. Start at Harajuku Station.",
    "Day 1 afternoon: Meiji Jingu shrine — 15-min walk from Omotesando, through the forest. Traditional contrast to the morning's modernism.",
    "Day 2 morning: Shinjuku — Mode Gakuen Cocoon Tower (exterior), Tokyo Met Gov Building (free observation deck opens 9:30). Then walk to Yoyogi Gymnasium.",
    "Day 2 afternoon: Asakusa — Senso-ji temple complex, then walk across Sumida River to Tokyo Skytree plaza (Nikken Sekkei design).",
    "Optional evening: Roppongi — 21_21 Design Sight if open, then Mori Tower observation deck for night skyline."
  ]

