  yield findings ≡ "Tokyo's transit system (JR Yamanote line + Metro) makes most areas reachable in 20-40 minutes, but neighborhood clustering saves hours.

HIGH-OVERLAP CLUSTERS (ramen + architecture in walking distance):
1. Shinjuku cluster: Fuunji (tsukemen) + Cocoon Tower + Met Gov Building + Yoyogi area. Dense, walkable.
2. Ebisu-Omotesando corridor: Afuri (ramen) + Omotesando starchitect row + Daikanyama T-Site (Klein Dytham). Connected by Yamanote (1 stop) or 20-min walk through Shibuya.
3. Ginza cluster: Kagari (ramen) + Shizuoka Press Building + Ginza Six + Kabuki-za theater (Kengo Kuma). Walkable.
4. Asakusa-Skytree axis: Multiple ramen shops + Senso-ji + Tokyo Skytree. Connected by walk across Sumida River.

TRANSIT MAP:
- Shinjuku → Harajuku/Omotesando: JR Yamanote 1 stop (3 min) or walk (20 min through Meiji Park)
- Omotesando → Ebisu: Metro Ginza line to Hibiya line (10 min)
- Shinjuku → Ginza: Metro Marunouchi line direct (15 min)
- Ginza → Asakusa: Metro Ginza line direct (15 min)
- Asakusa → Shinjuku: Metro + JR (30 min)

IC CARD: Get a Suica or Pasmo at the airport — works on all transit, many shops and vending machines."

  yield recommendations ≡ [
