  yield draft-plan ≡ "
WEEKEND TOKYO: RAMEN & ARCHITECTURE

=== DAY 1 (Saturday) — West Tokyo Loop ===

MORNING (9:00-11:30) — Omotesando Architecture Walk
- 9:00: Start at Harajuku Station (JR Yamanote)
- 9:15: Walk Omotesando boulevard — Prada building (Herzog & de Meuron),
  Tod's (Toyo Ito), Dior (SANAA), Omotesando Hills (Tadao Ando)
- 10:30: Continue to Cat Street area, Daikanyama T-Site if time
- 10:45: Walk toward Shinjuku. Head to Fuunji.

LUNCH (11:00-12:30) — Fuunji Tsukemen, Shinjuku
- 10:45: Queue at Fuunji (expect 30-45 min wait)
- Ticket machine: get the tsukemen (つけめん), size medium (中)
- Rich, thick fish-based dipping broth. Slurp loudly — it's polite.

AFTERNOON (13:00-17:00) — Shrines & Towers
- 13:00: Meiji Jingu shrine — walk through the torii gate forest.
  Traditional architecture: cypress wood, copper roof.
  Weekend bonus: may see a Shinto wedding procession.
- 14:30: JR Yamanote 1 stop to Shinjuku
- 15:00: Mode Gakuen Cocoon Tower — exterior photography
- 15:30: Tokyo Metropolitan Government Building — free observation deck
  (45th floor, open until 11pm). Clear day = Mt. Fuji visible.

DINNER (18:00-19:30) — Afuri Yuzu Shio, Ebisu
- 17:45: JR Yamanote from Shinjuku to Ebisu (2 stops, 5 min)
- 18:00: Afuri Ebisu — yuzu-citrus shio ramen. Lighter, aromatic.
  Counter seating, intimate. Good evening option after a heavy lunch tsukemen.
- 19:30: Evening stroll through Ebisu Garden Place (architecture)

=== DAY 2 (Sunday) — East Tokyo Linear ===

MORNING (9:00-11:30) — Shinjuku to Ginza
- 9:00: Revisit Cocoon Tower in morning light (optional)
- 9:30: Metro Marunouchi line from Shinjuku to Ginza (15 min)
- 10:00: Ginza architecture walk — Ginza Six (MVRDV rooftop garden),
  Shizuoka Press Building (Kenzo Tange, metabolist movement),
  Kabuki-za theater (Kengo Kuma renovation)

LUNCH (11:30-13:00) — Kagari Chicken Paitan, Ginza
- 11:30: Kagari (銀座 篝) — rich chicken-based paitan soba.
  Refined, Ginza-appropriate. Shorter weekend queue than weekday.
  Ticket machine ordering.

AFTERNOON (13:30-17:00) — Asakusa & Skytree
- 13:30: Metro Ginza line from Ginza to Asakusa (15 min)
- 14:00: Senso-ji temple complex — Kaminarimon (Thunder Gate),
  Nakamise shopping street, five-story pagoda, main hall.
  Tokyo's oldest temple (628 CE original).
- 15:30: Walk across Sumida River — views of Tokyo Skytree
